#id=1
#text=In the late spring , I bought a beautiful little tree from a nursery .
#id=2
#text=The workers there helped me find a type of tree that would grow tall and give good shade in the summer .
#id=3
#text=When I went home , I thought about the best place in my backyard to put the tree .
#id=4
#text=The tree 's roots were tied up in a little bag with some potting soil to give it water and nutrients for a little while , but it had to be put in the ground soon to keep it healthy .
#id=5
#text=I went to my garden shed and got some tools so I could plant it as soon as possible .
#id=6
#text=First I got a big wheelbarrow to help me carry everything I needed .
#id=7
#text=In the wheelbarrow , I put the little tree , a shovel , a big watering can , and a garden rake .
#id=8
#text=Then I pushed it to the spot in my yard that I wanted to put the tree .
#id=9
#text=I took the tree and all the tools out of the wheelbarrow , except for the shovel .
#text=Then I pushed my wheelbarrow to my compost bin at the other side of my garden .
#text=I one by one , I scooped a shovelful of compost into my wheelbarrow until there was enough to fill a couple of buckets .
#text=The compost would help the tree get a head start on growing tall and healthy .
#text=I pushed the wheelbarrow back to where I wanted to plant the tree .
#text=Next , I had to dig a hole so the tree would be secure in the ground .
#text=I stuck the tip of the shovel in the ground and pushed down hard on it with my foot .
#text=The ground gave way , and I was able to scoop the dirt out of the way .
#text=I did this until I had a round hole over two feet deep .
#text=I put the tree in the hole , but it would not stand up straight , and instead leaned on one side of the hole .
#text=I slowly scooped compost and dirt into the hole , carefully adjusting the tree to stand upright again after each shovelful .
#text=I patted the earth down to keep it compact .
#text=After a lot of hard work , the hole was finally filled with dirt and compost , and the tree was standing upright and strong .
#text=I smoothed over the dirt and compost with my garden rake , then filled up the watering can with water from a hose .
#text=I slowly poured the water over the freshly raked dirt , letting the water soak into the ground .
#text=The tree was planted and ready to grow !
